WEBVTT

00:01.060 --> 00:03.502
(soft dramatic music)

00:04.747 --> 00:07.756
(buzzers ringing from afar)

00:16.091 --> 00:18.726
(door rattling)
- It's time.

00:34.593 --> 00:37.036
(rap song)

00:42.043 --> 00:44.543
(loud indistinct chatter)

00:48.791 --> 00:52.051
(squealing)
- Oh, my gosh.

00:52.202 --> 00:53.886
- So you want a bunny?

00:54.037 --> 00:57.056
- We already have a dog.
- Maybe your dog wants a bunny?

00:57.132 --> 00:59.058
- Maybe...

00:59.727 --> 01:00.951
- Yeah.

01:00.953 --> 01:02.227
Um, come on.

01:02.304 --> 01:04.379
- I know, I love you so much.

01:04.398 --> 01:08.358
I'm sorry.
- It's okay. Maybe next time.

01:09.978 --> 01:11.553
- So we have a dog now?

01:11.572 --> 01:13.997
- Yeah. Didn't you know?
- Yeah, no, I didn't.

01:13.999 --> 01:15.407
That was not--
- I had to say something.

01:15.484 --> 01:17.725
'Cause, you know, you were
getting that look on your face

01:17.745 --> 01:19.912
and I was losing
the will to say no.

01:19.988 --> 01:21.638
Plus I'll be the one
looking after it.

01:21.640 --> 01:24.065
- Yeah, you always say that but
I don't think it's true, really.

01:24.085 --> 01:25.733
I'm responsible.
(shouting)

01:25.753 --> 01:28.420
- Are you seeing this?
- Yeah.

01:28.572 --> 01:31.090
(man): White people are
under attack.

01:31.317 --> 01:34.835
The invasion across our borders
by the uneducated,

01:34.911 --> 01:40.432
the unskilled, the hordes
of pathetic people is
unchecked...

01:41.251 --> 01:42.843
(indistinct speech)

01:42.995 --> 01:44.010
- Oh, my God.

01:44.163 --> 01:45.979
(shouting)

01:47.757 --> 01:50.016
Oh, my God, dude,
it's Sunday.

01:50.169 --> 01:52.260
Go to brunch.

01:52.279 --> 01:55.263
(man): Stand your ground.
Stand your ground!

01:55.341 --> 01:57.116
(engine starting)

01:59.120 --> 02:01.528
As long as one white man lives,

02:01.605 --> 02:04.623
all of our land will never be
your land

02:04.700 --> 02:07.442
and you will never replace us.

02:07.461 --> 02:09.795
- Okay, babe, seriously,
can we please go?

02:09.946 --> 02:11.121
Aaliyah!

02:11.781 --> 02:13.023
Please.
- Are you okay?

02:13.116 --> 02:16.042
- No. No, I'm not. Can we go?
- Yes, we can go.

02:16.119 --> 02:17.785
It's okay.

02:17.863 --> 02:20.806
- It's really not.
It's not okay.
- Hey, hey, hey... it's okay.

02:20.883 --> 02:24.384
- No, it's not.
That's why I moved here,
to get away from that.

02:24.461 --> 02:26.145
Can we just...
I just really want to go home.

02:26.296 --> 02:28.054
- You wanna go?
- Yeah, I do.

02:28.207 --> 02:30.207
- Okay, we'll go home.

02:30.209 --> 02:33.735
(tires screeching)
(crowd shouting in fear)

02:52.673 --> 02:54.756
(beeping)

03:05.093 --> 03:07.686
(key rattling in the door)

03:09.748 --> 03:11.765
- Still at it?
- Yeah, I think
I have something.

03:11.841 --> 03:15.085
I'm talking to this guy
who was there at the scene.

03:15.087 --> 03:17.362
- Well, who says he was there.

03:17.589 --> 03:19.180
- Nuh-uh. No.

03:19.258 --> 03:21.033
No. He... he knows things.

03:21.109 --> 03:23.610
Details.
I think he knows the driver.

03:23.762 --> 03:25.996
- Wait, is that you?

03:28.100 --> 03:30.459
White Future?

03:35.457 --> 03:37.365
Do you really think
this is healthy?

03:37.443 --> 03:40.594
Trolling the internet
as a white supremacist?

03:42.965 --> 03:44.297
Sweetie...

03:44.374 --> 03:46.874
you've been at this
for a week now.

03:46.894 --> 03:48.468
It's driving you crazy.

03:48.620 --> 03:50.562
No, the fact that our friend
Jordan is in a body cast

03:50.639 --> 03:53.123
and may never walk again
is driving me crazy.

03:53.125 --> 03:55.959
The police doing nothing,

03:55.961 --> 03:57.461
that's driving me crazy.

03:57.479 --> 04:02.056
And do you wanna know what's
driving me the most crazy?

04:02.634 --> 04:04.726
It's all the people
that were there that day

04:04.803 --> 04:07.320
saying how incensed they are

04:07.397 --> 04:09.706
but not doing a damn thing
about it.

04:17.833 --> 04:19.424
Hey...

04:20.152 --> 04:22.152
I just...

04:22.154 --> 04:24.471
Look, I didn't mean you.

04:25.766 --> 04:28.416
- I'm upset about it too, okay?

04:29.344 --> 04:32.512
I'm not saying that
we ignore it. I just...

04:32.664 --> 04:35.181
I don't want to see you
get swallowed up.

04:35.925 --> 04:38.593
There's no bottom to this,
it's toxic.

04:38.612 --> 04:41.154
I lived with it, I know.

04:42.599 --> 04:45.284
Just being around it
will destroy you.

04:45.360 --> 04:49.413
And now you're in it, 24/7.

04:51.941 --> 04:53.792
(sighs)
- Okay. Alright.

04:53.943 --> 04:55.276
Hey...

04:56.112 --> 05:00.716
Let's just... forget about
all of that for right now, okay?

05:01.527 --> 05:03.393
I'm here.

05:03.637 --> 05:05.470
I'm here with you.

05:09.384 --> 05:13.127
- Uh, maybe you could be like...
here with me.

05:13.147 --> 05:15.981
- Possibly.
(chuckling)

05:17.801 --> 05:19.609
- Oh, my God.

05:21.805 --> 05:24.531
(pop music)

05:26.660 --> 05:29.036
(indistinct PA announcement)

05:30.814 --> 05:33.206
(buzzer ringing)

05:44.403 --> 05:48.421
- Oh, baby,
what's the occasion?

05:48.498 --> 05:50.256
- Um, peace.

05:50.409 --> 05:51.666
- Hmm.

05:51.743 --> 05:53.243
- Has there been a war?

05:53.261 --> 05:55.187
- Uh, you know what I mean.

05:55.414 --> 05:57.931
And look you're not the only one

05:58.083 --> 06:01.526
who's been acting a little crazy
ever since we were almost
run over.

06:02.029 --> 06:05.030
I think I let this stuff
get to me

06:05.257 --> 06:06.681
more than I realized

06:06.700 --> 06:10.494
and I'm really sorry
if I took it out on you.

06:11.947 --> 06:13.538
(beeping)

06:15.117 --> 06:16.766
Is that...?
- I... I'm sorry.

06:16.785 --> 06:20.194
I just, he's... this is when
he said he'd be back online.

06:20.864 --> 06:23.882
- I... I thought you said
you were giving this stuff up?

06:23.959 --> 06:26.109
- I am.
I am.

06:26.111 --> 06:28.795
I just I need
to find the driver.

06:28.872 --> 06:31.056
- Okay. Now...

06:32.300 --> 06:34.041
- What are you...
what are you doing?

06:34.043 --> 06:36.061
- Were you even listening to me?

06:37.881 --> 06:39.639
You know what?
Forget it. Seriously.

06:40.308 --> 06:42.475
- What are you doing?
- I'm going out.

06:42.552 --> 06:44.310
- What? You can't.
- What do you mean I can't.

06:44.463 --> 06:46.405
- Wait, you can't.
Really, hey.

06:46.481 --> 06:48.573
- Yes, I can.
- Wait, wait, wait.

06:48.725 --> 06:50.150
He's here.

06:50.302 --> 06:52.744
- W... who's here?
- Uh, the guy.

06:52.896 --> 06:55.580
Um, the guy
I've been talking to.

06:55.732 --> 06:58.232
- You told him where we live?

06:58.310 --> 07:00.160
- No, I... of course not.

07:00.312 --> 07:02.587
- Well then,
how did he get here?

07:03.424 --> 07:05.632
- I don't know.

07:08.262 --> 07:10.137
(scoffs)

07:14.292 --> 07:17.185
- Is that him?
(beeping)

07:21.442 --> 07:22.666
What'd he say?

07:22.668 --> 07:25.835
(beeping)
- Um, he wants to meet me.

07:25.929 --> 07:29.764
- You can't. He thinks that
you're a white supremacist.

07:29.783 --> 07:31.700
- I know.

07:34.029 --> 07:36.496
I can't meet him...

07:37.440 --> 07:39.166
but you can.

07:41.687 --> 07:44.278
- No.
I'm not doing it.

07:44.356 --> 07:46.965
- Essie, somebody has
to go down there.

07:47.709 --> 07:49.542
Look...

07:49.619 --> 07:52.954
when that guy points his car
towards the crowd,

07:53.031 --> 07:54.864
he's not aiming for you.

07:54.883 --> 07:56.716
He's aiming for me.

07:56.793 --> 07:58.602
People like me.

07:59.980 --> 08:01.646
That guy down there,

08:01.723 --> 08:04.691
I know he was there
and I know he knows things.

08:05.802 --> 08:07.110
Please.

08:07.896 --> 08:09.529
Please, Essie.

08:23.003 --> 08:24.836
- White Future?

08:24.913 --> 08:26.320
- 88?

08:26.398 --> 08:29.065
- I'm sorry for just
showin' up unannounced.

08:29.084 --> 08:30.583
- Yeah well, you should be.

08:30.660 --> 08:32.511
- I didn't mean to scare you,
I just...

08:32.662 --> 08:34.996
I had to make sure you are
who you say you are.

08:36.758 --> 08:40.227
- You're not expecting me
to invite a stranger
up to my apartment, are you?

08:40.687 --> 08:43.980
- I mean, I take exception
to the word stranger.

08:45.341 --> 08:47.767
C'mon let's just
at least grab a drink,

08:47.919 --> 08:50.487
I've come all this way.

08:58.096 --> 08:59.279
(buzzer ringing)

08:59.355 --> 09:01.656
- Alright, let me just...
thank you.

09:02.434 --> 09:04.376
I have got some good news.

09:04.527 --> 09:07.287
The DA came in
with a new settlement offer.

09:07.439 --> 09:10.048
He's willing to take
first-degree murder
off the table

09:10.199 --> 09:11.608
if you plead to second.

09:11.610 --> 09:13.610
But he'll need you
to make a statement.

09:13.612 --> 09:15.720
Just a formal
expression of remorse.

09:15.872 --> 09:17.556
- No.

09:17.707 --> 09:19.616
- Esme.
- No way.

09:19.634 --> 09:21.726
I don't regret what I did.

09:23.121 --> 09:25.955
- Esme, when you get rid
of first degree,

09:25.957 --> 09:29.067
life without the possibility
of parole goes away too.

09:29.144 --> 09:30.643
As your attorney,

09:30.796 --> 09:34.531
I strongly recommend that you
give this some serious thought.

09:36.818 --> 09:39.226
- There's nothing
to think about.

09:39.246 --> 09:41.496
- Esme, are you sure?

09:43.083 --> 09:45.125
- I'm sure.

09:47.403 --> 09:48.962
Okay...

09:49.648 --> 09:51.481
Well, put this on.

09:51.499 --> 09:54.426
Your trial starts
in a half an hour.

09:57.839 --> 09:59.472
(buzzer ringing)

09:59.933 --> 10:01.725
Thank you.

10:03.495 --> 10:06.062
(theme music)

10:19.010 --> 10:20.785
(hard rock music)

10:20.937 --> 10:22.436
- I'm sorry if I spooked you.

10:22.530 --> 10:25.648
I just, I thought you were kinda
pushing for us to get together.

10:26.034 --> 10:27.867
- Maybe I was.

10:28.795 --> 10:31.278
So did you uh,
track my IP address?

10:31.373 --> 10:34.448
- Well, I half expected you
to be a cop.

10:34.468 --> 10:36.468
It all seemed
too good to be true.

10:36.544 --> 10:37.952
- Then why'd you come?

10:38.029 --> 10:39.971
- Guess I had a hunch
you'd be worth it.

10:40.048 --> 10:43.058
Hell, what are the odds, right?

10:44.978 --> 10:46.728
"Holy Waters?"

10:48.464 --> 10:50.131
- The Bible Camp.

10:50.150 --> 10:52.725
- Concentration camp,
if you ask me.

10:53.561 --> 10:56.988
Yeah, I can't believe
I told you I went there.

10:57.140 --> 10:59.115
- It's a small world, huh?

10:59.901 --> 11:01.809
It feels kinda cosmic.

11:01.887 --> 11:03.403
The two of us.

11:04.331 --> 11:06.814
- You think you're
pretty charming, don't you?

11:06.833 --> 11:08.333
- Is it working?

11:08.484 --> 11:10.627
(chuckles)

11:12.397 --> 11:16.749
So tell me... what's a girl
like you even doing here?

11:16.902 --> 11:18.735
- Making a living.

11:18.753 --> 11:20.327
- Yeah, but how do you stand it?

11:20.405 --> 11:22.681
You know, the smell of 'em.
- Hmm...

11:22.832 --> 11:26.576
- Just walking down the street,
they leave a residue.

11:26.594 --> 11:30.689
- Yeah, I mean "If it's brown,
flush it down" right?

11:30.765 --> 11:33.266
My daddy had that
on his bumper.

11:33.342 --> 11:35.694
Back when we were allowed
to have free speech.

11:35.845 --> 11:37.696
- Amen.
(chuckles)

11:37.772 --> 11:39.422
(bottles tinkling)

11:40.701 --> 11:45.352
- You know, I, um...
I have to admit I was
a little bit jealous.

11:45.430 --> 11:47.096
- Of?

11:47.098 --> 11:50.625
- Well, you were there
when it happened.

11:52.270 --> 11:54.754
Driver a friend of yours?

11:55.774 --> 11:56.773
- Maybe.

11:56.791 --> 11:59.884
- Or maybe you are being modest.

12:00.628 --> 12:03.096
- The truth?
- Mm-hmm.

12:04.057 --> 12:05.615
I don't think it was worth it.

12:05.633 --> 12:08.509
All that heat, over what?
A drop in the bucket.

12:09.563 --> 12:12.605
We've got somethin'
much bigger planned.

12:13.308 --> 12:15.308
- Oh yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

12:15.460 --> 12:17.885
What do you say
I get us another round?

12:17.963 --> 12:19.696
- Yeah.

12:30.751 --> 12:34.477
(door opening)
You know you really could have
warned me?

12:34.479 --> 12:37.905
- There wasn't any time. I just,
everything happened so fast.

12:37.924 --> 12:39.573
- He knew everything about me.

12:39.651 --> 12:42.260
You used my whole life.
- Essie, I'm sorry.

12:42.337 --> 12:44.929
I'm so sorry.
Really, I...

12:45.932 --> 12:48.508
Look, I only did it because
I needed him to trust me.

12:48.584 --> 12:50.727
I'm sorry, Essie.

12:51.997 --> 12:54.013
Are you okay?

12:54.165 --> 12:56.149
- I'm calling the police.

12:59.521 --> 13:01.270
- So that's him?

13:02.431 --> 13:04.115
- And he says he's planning
something else.

13:04.192 --> 13:06.534
Something big.

13:09.105 --> 13:11.105
- So what's his name?

13:11.124 --> 13:14.017
- Uh, 88 is his handle. 88.

13:14.019 --> 13:15.518
- 88?

13:15.537 --> 13:18.704
You sat with this guy how long
and you didn't get his name?

13:18.857 --> 13:22.300
- No, if I had asked him he
would have gotten up and left.

13:23.303 --> 13:26.287
Look, he's dangerous.
I know him.

13:26.364 --> 13:28.548
I mean, not him specifically

13:28.550 --> 13:32.459
but we went to the same bible
camp and he says he knows the
driver who ran down our friend.

13:32.479 --> 13:34.871
- I mean, he may even be
the driver.

13:34.964 --> 13:36.297
- Yeah.

13:36.316 --> 13:39.225
- He knows things like
the cracked windshield.

13:40.320 --> 13:43.229
- Maybe he watched the video.
A lot of people did.

13:43.306 --> 13:45.472
Look, look, look, he says
he lives upstate

13:45.567 --> 13:48.267
with some people at a compound,
or a farm or something.

13:48.328 --> 13:49.810
We think that's
where the car is.

13:49.830 --> 13:52.163
- And you want me to drop
everything and track him down

13:52.315 --> 13:54.207
for meeting you at a bar.

13:55.393 --> 13:57.318
- You're not going to do
anything, are you?

13:57.337 --> 13:59.987
- What I am gonna do is tell you
to stop playing detective.

14:00.065 --> 14:01.488
- I'm not playing!

14:01.566 --> 14:03.399
- Anything comes up,
we'll let you know, okay?

14:03.418 --> 14:07.095
In the meantime,
let us do our job, okay?

14:09.924 --> 14:13.017
(door closing)
- He's not gonna do anything.

14:14.020 --> 14:16.913
- Yeah, well...

14:17.415 --> 14:20.358
it's kinda how it goes,
isn't it?

14:21.027 --> 14:23.753
But hey, you were right.

14:24.439 --> 14:27.699
I never should have invited
that guy into our lives.

14:29.094 --> 14:32.036
I'm sorry I put you
in that position, okay?

14:32.764 --> 14:35.081
Look, let's just drop it now.

14:35.934 --> 14:37.625
Yeah?

14:56.396 --> 14:58.212
- Hey, you okay?

14:58.289 --> 15:00.565
- Yeah.
- Okay.

15:01.292 --> 15:02.734
(man): All rise.

15:02.885 --> 15:06.145
Department Seventy
of the Superior Court is now
in session,

15:06.297 --> 15:08.740
Judge Morse presiding.

15:15.916 --> 15:17.999
- What are you doing?

15:19.160 --> 15:22.003
- I've been talking to him.

15:23.498 --> 15:25.148
- Are you serious?

15:25.150 --> 15:26.925
Uh... Essie.

15:27.076 --> 15:30.678
- He invited me upstate
to their compound where he lives
with those people.

15:33.508 --> 15:34.674
- You...

15:34.993 --> 15:37.251
But you're not actually
thinking about going, right?

15:37.328 --> 15:38.661
- It's like you said.

15:38.754 --> 15:41.105
Everyone's so mad about it
but nobody's doing anything.

15:41.182 --> 15:44.684
And now they're planning
on doing something else
and the cops won't get involved.

15:44.760 --> 15:46.185
I can't...
I can't let that happen.

15:46.337 --> 15:49.839
- Essie...
- Listen, listen to me, baby.

15:49.857 --> 15:51.841
(Essie sighs.)

15:51.843 --> 15:53.526
When I was a kid...

15:54.437 --> 15:57.196
I was riding with my brother
Charlie

15:57.290 --> 16:00.166
and there was this black kid
on the corner.

16:02.036 --> 16:03.628
Charlie just...

16:03.705 --> 16:06.089
threw a bottle at his head.

16:07.525 --> 16:10.784
The kid screamed,
charged at us,

16:10.862 --> 16:14.514
he didn't know there was a truck
full of Charlie's buddies
right behind us.

16:17.202 --> 16:19.143
They all got out and...

16:19.220 --> 16:21.562
started kicking
the hell outta him.

16:22.298 --> 16:24.207
And he was screaming.

16:24.559 --> 16:28.444
And there was...
blood all over the street.

16:31.065 --> 16:33.324
And you know what I did?

16:36.329 --> 16:38.037
Nothing.

16:38.498 --> 16:40.540
I just watched.

16:43.077 --> 16:45.086
- You were a kid.

16:45.913 --> 16:47.839
- But I'm not anymore.

16:47.915 --> 16:49.398
- Essie...

16:49.417 --> 16:52.552
please, you cannot go with him.

16:53.254 --> 16:55.638
- I already said yes.

16:56.332 --> 16:58.224
(beeping)

17:08.419 --> 17:10.194
He's here.

17:12.273 --> 17:14.924
- Okay.
- But what are you doing?

17:14.926 --> 17:16.200
- No, no, no. No, no.

17:16.352 --> 17:18.110
- I'm gonna show him who
he's really been talking to.

17:18.187 --> 17:19.871
- So then what?
So then you get killed?

17:20.022 --> 17:21.781
And they get away with it?

17:21.933 --> 17:23.708
Listen to me,

17:23.859 --> 17:26.360
Okay? My whole life,

17:26.379 --> 17:31.332
I thought I was brave
for getting out but I wasn't.

17:31.367 --> 17:34.443
I was always just running.

17:34.462 --> 17:36.763
Scared. Always.

17:37.632 --> 17:39.599
And I'm sick of it.

17:42.062 --> 17:44.062
I love you.

17:46.140 --> 17:48.066
I love you, okay?

17:48.068 --> 17:51.611
I need to go.
- No, please don't go.

17:52.555 --> 17:54.238
- I need to go, okay?

17:54.465 --> 17:57.366
Look, look, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

18:10.481 --> 18:12.757
Oh. Okay.

18:12.908 --> 18:14.759
- Don't be shy.

18:14.986 --> 18:16.485
Your boyfriend sent me.

18:16.504 --> 18:20.172
- Uh, he's not my boyfriend.
I don't even know his name.

18:20.249 --> 18:23.017
- And I don't know your name.

18:24.345 --> 18:26.086
- I'm Esme.

18:26.106 --> 18:27.772
People call me Essie.

18:28.666 --> 18:30.942
- Isn't that what Mexicans
call each other?

18:31.018 --> 18:33.927
- No, I think that's Ess-ay.

18:33.947 --> 18:35.521
- I'm messing with you.

18:35.598 --> 18:39.075
But the question is,
are you messing with me?

18:41.103 --> 18:42.620
- What's that supposed to mean?

18:42.697 --> 18:45.790
- It means my boy comes back
from the big city

18:45.941 --> 18:48.942
