you had been on the phone
with her

39:51.281 --> 39:53.965
for nearly four minutes.

39:53.967 --> 39:56.059
Does that sound right?

39:57.044 --> 39:59.454
- I... yeah, I guess so.

39:59.472 --> 40:01.046
- And during that time,

40:01.307 --> 40:05.527
did the defendant relate to you
what she planned
to do to the victims?

40:07.555 --> 40:09.221
- They weren't victims.

40:09.241 --> 40:12.492
- To the deceased then.

40:15.914 --> 40:18.581
Would you like me
to repeat the question?

40:20.735 --> 40:22.377
Ms. Williams?

40:23.755 --> 40:25.404
- Ms. Williams.

40:25.482 --> 40:27.573
You will answer the question.

40:27.592 --> 40:31.136
Did the defendant relate to you
what she planned to do?

40:32.656 --> 40:35.598
Ms. Williams, you will answer
the question

40:35.675 --> 40:37.267
or I will find you in contempt,

40:37.343 --> 40:40.728
and you'll both be behind bars,
do you understand?

40:43.833 --> 40:46.258
Ms. Williams,
you're leaving me no choice.

40:46.278 --> 40:48.093
The court instructs
the bailiff to--

40:48.113 --> 40:50.029
- She said...

40:51.858 --> 40:54.451
She said, "I see them."

40:55.787 --> 40:58.288
"I see the two men who ran us
down in the street."

40:58.439 --> 41:00.515
- Your Honor, the victims are
not the ones on trial here.

41:00.533 --> 41:02.608
- "I see the two men who killed
innocent people with a bomb

41:02.686 --> 41:04.443
they were too cowardly
to deliver themselves."

41:04.463 --> 41:06.629
- Move to strike.
- She said,

41:06.781 --> 41:07.797
"I see them."

41:08.191 --> 41:11.342
- Ms. Williams. I remind you
that you are under oath.

41:12.971 --> 41:14.721
- Yeah.

41:16.382 --> 41:18.725
Yeah, you don't need
to remind me.

41:20.645 --> 41:23.730
Don't need to remind me
where I am right now.

41:30.730 --> 41:32.489
Baby...

41:34.234 --> 41:36.576
Let's go home, Essie.

41:39.556 --> 41:41.456
Let's go home.

41:43.835 --> 41:46.753
We were so happy
just the two of us.

41:50.233 --> 41:52.967
I never thought I could be
that happy...

41:55.255 --> 41:58.014
and I'm just so scared
to lose you.

42:00.076 --> 42:03.186
<i> (people shouting)</i>

42:09.694 --> 42:11.510
- You've got to trust the jury.

42:11.530 --> 42:14.346
I mean, the facts in this case
were overwhelming.

42:14.366 --> 42:16.607
Esme Barnes laid in wait
for nearly two weeks

42:16.701 --> 42:20.444
before running two men down in
cold blood with an automobile.

42:20.597 --> 42:24.857
It's difficult to even imagine
a clearer example
of premeditation,

42:24.934 --> 42:31.030
and the jury arrived at the
only possible verdict, guilty.

42:31.049 --> 42:35.367
- But a lot of people see
Esme Barnes as a hero,
so what would you say to them?

42:35.387 --> 42:40.473
- I would ask them to take a
long hard look at the kind of
world that they want to live in.

42:42.209 --> 42:43.893
<i> Two more people are dead.</i>

42:44.971 --> 42:50.400
<i> Two people who were planning</i>
<i> to build a life together now</i>
<i> never will.</i>

42:51.719 --> 42:55.655
<i> And I have to believe</i>
<i> that we can do better.</i>
